"{\"uid\": \"boredpanda.com-mass-fall-olympic-runners-mens-5000m-leads-physical-altercation\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"No fees, cancel anytime    Log In  or    Sign Up  or      Reset your password  Enter your email address or username and we will send you a link to reset your password  Check your inbox  An email with a link to reset your password was sent to the email address associated with your account  Provide email  Please enter your email to complete registration    Activate to continue  Your account is not active yet.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 410, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We have emailed you an activation link.\", \"from\": 411, \"to\": 450, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please check your inbox and click the link to activate your account      The Bored Panda iOS app is live!Fight boredom with iPhones and iPadshere.\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 597, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 575, \"end\": 582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IPhone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"iPhones\", \"types\": [\"Q1067263\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IPhone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IPhone\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Join 1.2 million Panda readers who get the best art, memes, and fun stories every week!\", \"from\": 599, \"to\": 686, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"P.S.\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 692, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's 100% free, unsubscribe anytime.\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 729, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You are on the list!\", \"from\": 731, \"to\": 751, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Expect to receive your first email very soon!\", \"from\": 752, \"to\": 797, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Discover trivia, brain teasers, and quirky quizzes - fresh every week!\", \"from\": 799, \"to\": 869, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We value your inbox - it's free and you can unsubscribe anytime with one click.\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 950, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"20  2  Link copied!\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 971, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Share  Link copied!\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 992, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Share  Olympic runnersGeorge Millsfrom Great Britain andHugo Hayfrom France exchanged elbows during the latest 5000m qualifying heat, resulting in a domino effect that caused four other athletes to fall and the rest to scramble to continue amid the chaos.\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 1249, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1063, \"end\": 1069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9937302021373772, \"rank\": 0.005987243952195788, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hay remained upright and continued running, but Mills, alongside Thierry Ndikumwenayo from Spain, Dominic Lokinyomo from the Refugee Team, Moh Ahmed from Canada, and Mike Foppen from the Netherlands, fell on the tracks and were thus unable to compete properly.\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1513, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1318, \"end\": 1338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thierry_Ndikumwenayo\", \"score\": 0.9999987278196293, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thierry Ndikumwenayo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thierry_Ndikumwenayo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thierry_Ndikumwenayo\"}, {\"begin\": 1344, \"end\": 1349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9959518829141782, \"rank\": 0.004059140883724596, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1378, \"end\": 1390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Refugee Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1407, \"end\": 1413, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999998987923442, \"rank\": 9.025129184106474e-08, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 1440, \"end\": 1451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9992670691516665, \"rank\": 0.0007170450995364391, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After crossing the finish line, Mills caught up to Hay and reportedly shouted obscenities while furiously pointing his finger at him.\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1648, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am probably not allowed to [reveal] what I said,\\\" the athlete told theBBC.\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1727, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"TheBritish athletewould later explain that he believed Hay pushed him aside in order to try to break ahead, causing his legs to get tangled up.\", \"from\": 1729, \"to\": 1872, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Image credits:Olympics    \\\"I think it's pretty clear.\", \"from\": 1876, \"to\": 1929, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I got stepped out on as I was about to kick in the home straight and boom, theFrench ladtook me down.\\\"\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 2032, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Upon reviewing theincident, judges decided to reinstate four of the affected competitors, with only Canada's Moh Ahmed having his appealdenied.\", \"from\": 2034, \"to\": 2177, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2134, \"end\": 2140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 0.9999998987923442, \"rank\": 9.025129184106474e-08, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mills, on the other hand, believes that the measure ultimately had nothing to do with his qualification, as heexpressed confidencein his ability to win theracehad the accident not happened.\", \"from\": 2179, \"to\": 2368, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Image credits:Petersen/Getty  \\\"From my perspective that was the perfect qualifier for me, going through the first 2k in six minutes.\", \"from\": 2372, \"to\": 2504, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was like: 'Nobody in this field can run away from me at this pace', so I was just sitting, waiting, biding my time, gonna kick off the home straight then bang, hit the deck.\", \"from\": 2505, \"to\": 2680, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What can you do?\\\"\", \"from\": 2681, \"to\": 2698, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some experts, such as formerOlympicsilver medallist Steve Cram, were not as sure as Mills and expressed their doubts about his performance.\", \"from\": 2700, \"to\": 2839, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2752, \"end\": 2762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Cram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Steve Cram\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Cram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Steve_Cram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"George was in a bad position from a long way out, he should have checked out much earlier,\\\" Cram explained.\", \"from\": 2841, \"to\": 2949, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is lots of experienced men in there and yes, everyone thinks they can kick, but when you get to that situation [very slow pace] the chances of people going down are incredibly increased.\\\"\", \"from\": 2951, \"to\": 3145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Image credits:georgemills800  Hugo Hay would later categorically deny the accusations in an interview withEurosport,explaining that he made contact with his opponent as a result of being pushed around by other competitors.\", \"from\": 3149, \"to\": 3371, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"At the end, there was a big pile-up,\\\" heexplained.\", \"from\": 3373, \"to\": 3424, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Englishman came to tell me it was my fault, so I went to look at the slow-motion replay.\", \"from\": 3425, \"to\": 3518, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As far as I am concerned, it was someone else who pushed me and I just put my elbow in.\\\"\", \"from\": 3519, \"to\": 3607, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Image credits:georgemills800  The accidents would continue in the next heat of the event, as at one point, a cameraman was seen wandering into the path of the runners midway through therace, making them suddenly change course.\", \"from\": 3611, \"to\": 3837, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Another athlete, American Abdihamid Nur, also fell and ultimatelyfinished last.\", \"from\": 3839, \"to\": 3918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3856, \"end\": 3864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999997124391897, \"rank\": 2.8623318189954374e-07, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3875, \"end\": 3878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nur_Ahmed_Aman\", \"score\": 0.9999999994397513, \"rank\": 5.60183669451133e-10, \"text\": \"Nur\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nur_Ahmed_Aman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nur_Ahmed_Aman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first place in the second qualifying event went to Jakob Ingebrigtsen from Norway, followed closely by Biniam Mehary from Ethiopia and Isaac Kimeli from Belgium.\", \"from\": 3920, \"to\": 4085, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3975, \"end\": 3993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jakob Ingebrigtsen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\"}, {\"begin\": 3999, \"end\": 4005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"score\": 0.999994179463215, \"rank\": 5.538315679437835e-06, \"text\": \"Norway\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\"}, {\"begin\": 4046, \"end\": 4054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9999513404038498, \"rank\": 4.857818596463379e-05, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 4059, \"end\": 4071, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isaac_Kimeli\", \"score\": 0.9999919459761817, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Isaac Kimeli\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isaac_Kimeli\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isaac_Kimeli\"}, {\"begin\": 4077, \"end\": 4084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9935823007436736, \"rank\": 0.006459141188992654, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The top places for the first qualifying event, in which the four-man accident took place, saw Norway's Narve Nordas, Ethiopia's Hagos Gebrhiwet, and Belgium's John Heymans arrive at first, second, and third places, respectively.\", \"from\": 4087, \"to\": 4315, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4181, \"end\": 4187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"score\": 0.999994179463215, \"rank\": 5.538315679437835e-06, \"text\": \"Norway\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\"}, {\"begin\": 4204, \"end\": 4212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9999513404038498, \"rank\": 4.857818596463379e-05, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 4236, \"end\": 4243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9935823007436736, \"rank\": 0.006459141188992654, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The finals of the 5000m men's long-running event will take place this Saturday (August 10), and it will come with the participation of a total of 20 athletes - as opposed to the usual 16 - due to the accident.\", \"from\": 4317, \"to\": 4526, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Image credits:hugo.hay  \\\"This was absolutely wild to watch.\", \"from\": 4530, \"to\": 4589, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I realize rules change with theOlympics, but if pushing and bumping is not allowed on the high-school track, why allow it for the Olympics?\\\"\", \"from\": 4590, \"to\": 4730, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"asked one viewer.\", \"from\": 4731, \"to\": 4748, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It looked like it was George Mills' fault but then he claimed he was 'moved out on' in the interview afterwards,\\\" theorized another.\", \"from\": 4750, \"to\": 4883, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Unfortunately this looks like George Mills' fault - got himself in a bad position and caused chaos trying to push to the front,\\\" said one journalist for theBBCon her X account.\", \"from\": 4885, \"to\": 5062, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Well, he has been reinstated by event organizers.\", \"from\": 5063, \"to\": 5113, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Shows what I know.\\\"\", \"from\": 5114, \"to\": 5133, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Look at it in slow-mo and you will see Hugo Hay pushes George Mills, then George's arm comes out to steady himself,\\\" replied one user.\", \"from\": 5135, \"to\": 5270, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Anyone can write on Bored Panda.Start writing!\", \"from\": 5290, \"to\": 5336, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Bored Panda onGoogle News!\", \"from\": 5338, \"to\": 5371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5345, \"end\": 5356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bored_Panda\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bored Panda\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bored_Panda\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bored_Panda\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow us onFlipboard.com/@boredpanda!\", \"from\": 5373, \"to\": 5411, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"20  2  20  2  Link copied!\", \"from\": 5415, \"to\": 5441, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Share  Link copied!\", \"from\": 5443, \"to\": 5462, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Share  Writer,Entertainment News Writer  Born in Santiago, Chile, with a background in communication and international relations, I bring a global perspective to entertainment reporting at Bored Panda.\", \"from\": 5464, \"to\": 5665, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5513, \"end\": 5521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santiago\", \"score\": 0.9999965736719368, \"rank\": 3.3860046159960842e-06, \"text\": \"Santiago\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santiago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santiago\"}, {\"begin\": 5523, \"end\": 5528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chile\", \"score\": 0.96903060